  "topic": "relationships",
  "title": "Thirty-Six Questions",
  "units": [
    {
      "t": "text",
      "l1": "Can two strangers fall in "
    },
    {
      "t": "weave",
      "l1": "love",
      "l2": "Liebe",
      "lemma": "Liebe",
      "pos": "noun",
      "gender": "f",
      "gloss": "love",
      "ipa": "ˈliːbə",
      "weave_priority": 5
    },
    {
      "t": "text",
      "l1": " on purpose? A psychologist named Arthur Aron believed they could. He built a list of thirty-six "
    },
    {
      "t": "weave",
      "l1": "questions",
      "l2": "Fragen",
      "lemma": "Frage",
      "pos": "noun",
      "gender": "f",
      "gloss": "question",
      "ipa": "ˈfʁaːɡə",
      "weave_priority": 4
    },
    {
      "t": "text",
      "l1": " that slowly grow more personal. Two "
    },
    {
      "t": "weave",
      "l1": "people",
      "l2": "Leute",
      "lemma": "Leute",
      "pos": "noun",
      "gloss": "people",
      "ipa": "ˈlɔʏtə",
      "weave_priority": 3
    },
    {
      "t": "text",
      "l1": " sit face to face and take turns asking them. The early questions are light and easy. Later ones ask about "
    },
    {
      "t": "weave",
      "l1": "family",
      "l2": "Familie",
      "lemma": "Familie",
      "pos": "noun",
      "gender": "f",
      "gloss": "family",
      "ipa": "faˈmiːli̯ə",
      "weave_priority": 5
    },
    {
      "t": "text",
      "l1": ", fear, and your deepest dreams. At the very end, the two partners look into each other's "
    },
    {
      "t": "weave",
      "l1": "eyes",
      "l2": "Augen",
      "lemma": "Auge",
      "pos": "noun",
      "gender": "n",
      "gloss": "eye",
      "ipa": "ˈaʊɡə",
      "weave_priority": 4
    },
    {
      "t": "text",
      "l1": " in silence for four long minutes. Many "
    },
    {
      "t": "weave",
      "l1": "couples",
      "l2": "Paare",
      "lemma": "Paar",
      "pos": "noun",
      "gender": "n",
      "gloss": "couple",
      "ipa": "paːɐ̯",
      "weave_priority": 6
    },
    {
      "t": "text",
      "l1": " who tried this said they felt surprisingly close afterwards. Some even married. The idea is simple but strong. Love does not only come by luck or by chance. It can also grow when two people choose to open their "
    },
    {
      "t": "weave",
      "l1": "hearts",
      "l2": "Herzen",
      "lemma": "Herz",
      "pos": "noun",
      "gender": "n",
      "gloss": "heart",
      "ipa": "hɛʁts",
      "weave_priority": 3
    },
    {
      "t": "text",
      "l1": " and share what they usually hide."
    }
  ]
}
